{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "8cb0d4d8-f7cb-4e86-93d0-3c20035f0033",
    "name": "Ingester Telephony Systems Supervisor",
    "description": "Local debugging collection for IngesterTelephonySystemsSupervisor.\n\nEntry points are triggered over HTTP against the running service (default local port 8097, Local profile, no context path).\n\nAUTH: This service is internal-only (publicFacing: False). No application-level auth filter is present locally — requests need no token/header.\n\nENTRY-POINT COVERAGE:\n\n- HTTP troubleshooters: triggered directly (this is what they are).\n    \n- Pull (scheduled sync / initial-import / SQS monitors / S3 cleaners): POST /troubleshooting/tasks/{taskId}/run. NOTE: ScheduledTask beans register only under DEV/PROD profiles, NOT Local. To use the tasks folder, run the service with -Dspring.profiles.active=DEV.\n    \n- Push (telephony-call-event consumer): process-one-event endpoint invokes the same dialerService.processCallEvent(...).\n    \n- Push (other 7 Kafka consumers): NO dedicated HTTP trigger. See the 'Kafka Consumers (reference)' folder — breakpoint accept() and produce to the topic, or breakpoint the downstream service.\n    \n\nFor the exhaustive endpoint list on a running instance, use Swagger: {{baseUrl}}/swagger-ui/index.html or {{baseUrl}}/v3/api-docs",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "_exporter_id": "56033112",
    "_collection_link": "https://go.postman.co/collection/56033112-8cb0d4d8-f7cb-4e86-93d0-3c20035f0033?source=collection_link"
  },
