    {
      "name": "Kafka Consumers (reference — NO direct HTTP trigger)",
      "item": [],
      "description": "These push entry points have NO dedicated troubleshooting HTTP endpoint. To hit them: set a breakpoint on the consumer's accept(ConsumerRecord) and produce a message to the topic, OR breakpoint the downstream service method.\n\n| Consumer | Topic | Cluster |\n|---|---|---|\n| TelephonyCallEventConsumer | gong-connect-dialer-events (KafkaTopics.DIALER_EVENTS) | TELEPHONY_SYSTEMS — has HTTP twin (process-one-event) |\n| LowPriorityTelephonyCallEventConsumer | low-priority-dialer-events | TELEPHONY_SYSTEMS |\n| GongConnectCallEventConsumer | gong-connect-call-event | TELEPHONY_SYSTEMS |\n| CompanyUpdatedConsumer | app-user-changes (APP_USER) | — |\n| MsTeamsAppUserChangesConsumer | app-user-changes | APP_USER |\n| CrmAssociationRetryConsumer | (retry topic) | — |\n| TelephonySystemsAssociationUpdatedConsumer | association-updated | ACTIVITY_CRM_ASSOCIATIONS |\n| TsNonRecordedCallsProcessingStatusConsumer | call-processing-status-event | CALL_PROCESSOR |\n\nBreakpoint target for all: the consumer's accept(...) method (e.g. TelephonyCallEventConsumerAbstract.java:46)."
    }
